Ghana stock exchange ends slightly firmer . The Ghana Stock Exchange ended the week marginally higher after another quiet session , dealers said . The Ghana All - Share Index added 0 . 42 point to 383 . 43 . Ghana Commercial Bank recovered 10 cedis of its recent loss , ending at 520 , on turnover of 35 , 000 shares , and Pioneer Tobacco added five to 305 . The most active stock was Enterprise Insurance , which ended five cedis higher at 555 with 180 , 100 shares changing hands . Among the losers , Ashanti Goldfields fell 400 cedis to 21 , 600 . Overall volume was a low 375 , 790 shares . - - Abidjan newsroom , + 225 21 90 90 
